  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nFor the filter in Don't Starve Together, see Light Sources Filter.\nTab Icon\n“Sure beats darkness.”\n–Wilson\nLight is used to illuminate the world at Night, lowering the rate at which Sanity decreases and protecting against Charlie, who will attack in total darkness.\nSee also: Light Sources\nDownloadable Content[edit | edit source]\nIn the Reign of Giants DLC, Endothermic Fires, Endothermic Fire Pits, and Moggles were added to the Light Tab.\nIn the Shipwrecked DLC, the player can craft Chimineas, Buoyant Chimineas, Tar Lamps, Obsidian Fire Pits and Bottle Lanterns in the Light Tab. This DLC also includes Endothermic Fires and Endothermic Fire Pits. Additionally, the two light sources that can be attached to Boats, Boat Torches and Boat Lanterns, are available in this tab.\nIn the Hamlet DLC, Cork Candle Hats and Cowls were added to this tab, while Pumpkin Lanterns are not available.\nCraftable Items and Structures[edit | edit source]\nThe following items and structures can be crafted in the Light Tab:\nCampfire\nFire Pit\nTorch\nMiner Hat\nPumpkin Lantern\nLantern\nEndothermic Fire\nEndothermic Fire Pit\nMoggles\nChiminea\nBuoyant Chiminea\nTar Lamp\nObsidian Fire Pit\nBottle Lantern\nBoat Torch\nBoat Lantern\nCork Candle Hat\nCowl\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Crafting Tabs\nRegular\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\n(Nautical )\n(Treasure Hunting )\nCharacter-Specific\nBooks\nTinkering\n(Green Thumb )\nNon-prototypable\nAncient\nVolcanic\n(Renovate\nCity Planning )",
